President Cyril Ramaphosa has ended the tenure in the National Prosecuting Authority of advocates Nomgcobo Jiba and Lawrence Mrwebi, as recommended by the Mokgoro inquiry into the fitness of the two officials to hold office. Ramaphosa wrote to the former deputy national director of public prosecutions and former head of the specialised commercial crime unit on Thursday informing them of his decision, saying he had accepted the recommendations of the Mokgoro inquiry that they should be removed. The panel was chaired by retired Constitutional Court Justice Yvonne Mokgoro. Read the full report below: Mokgoro Report - Unabridgedâ€¦ by  on Scribd 